scripts/make-app.sh: replaced ad-hoc `codesign --sign -` with auto-pick of the most stable codesign identity in the keychain (Developer ID Application > Apple Development > ad-hoc fallback). Ad-hoc signing was the root cause of the repeated Screen Recording prompts: ad-hoc DR is the cdhash which changes on every rebuild, invalidating the prior TCC grant. With a stable Developer ID identity the DR is identifier+leaf cert and TCC stays sticky.